race.comment: Looks a wide open affair. HEADHUNTER (9) returned in fine fashion with a strong win at the Sunny Coast and will appreciate the step-up to the mile journey now. Winning rider Guthmann-Chester stays on top and can make it back-to-back victories to start the campaign. DETRIMENTAL (3) got an overdue win last time out and will have derived a stack of confidence from that victory. Include with the 3kg claim. LARUSSO (12) strips fitter second-up from the spell and maps perfectly for this from gate three. In the mix. JEMOMA ALPILAGE (13) will be ready to peak now fourth run back and may earn some minor money. POSSIBILITIES (14) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on.
